@fadster when the HLS issues have been resolved we'll update the plugin to support HLS. It seems highly unlikely that the HLS streams as they are will stay around for too long. If they really did have 7Gbps upstream being using that will have been expensive and they'll wanna get that fixed asap. 
Granted, you can find it easily on the website or with a URL sniffer, but as a show of good faith towards vaughnsoft I think it's a good idea that we don't support HLS until they have it sorted - I don't want Streamlink to be a reason for them to have to shutdown. 

The way that the HLS stream URLs can be abused is that they do not require any authentication to access, while the RTMP streams require an "auth" token. Anyone can grab an HLS URL for a channel and share it with 14,000 people and it'll just work (for a while anyway), the RTMP URLs (`rtmpdump` parameters) require a token that expires fairly quickly so you cannot share it. Also, when you get the HLS URL it's for a specific server (1 out of 4), and if that URL gets shared all the connections go to that one server and vaughnsoft cannot do any load balancing.

