I reproduced your problem and may have found what causes it. (Pretty cool map by the way!)

If I get to zoom level 7, the tileserver responds with HTTP status 403 Forbidden for each tile. So Leaflet expects to receive tiles, is unable to get them, and then displays grey tiles. 

The same happens if you use OpenStreetMaps and go past zoom level 18 or 19 (I think), you get a HTTP status 404 Not Found on each tile.

A solution is to provide a `maxNativeZoom` option to the `tileLayer` function. It tells Leaflet to not retrieve tiles for zoom levels beyond this value. This is not implemented in Folium, so you will have to do it in the javascript that is created by Folium. For example:
```
var tile_layer_1234 = L.tileLayer(
                'https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/whereonmars.cartodb.net/mola-color/{z}/{x}/{-y}.png',
                {
  "attribution": "NASA/MOLA |<a href=\"https://github.com/openplanetary/opm/wiki/OPM-Basemaps\" target=\"blank\">OpenPlanetaryMap</a>",
  "maxNativeZoom": 6,
  "maxZoom": 18,
} ).addTo(map_1234);
```

